Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentended to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of twelve (12) years.  That is seven (7) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program after the defendant has served 2.5 years of his sentence.
Conditions of extended supervision:
The defendant has credit for 403 days.
1) maintain absolute sobriety;
2) maintain fulltime employment;
3) no contact with A-Store Convenience Store;
4) defendant is to have one doctor to prescribe medication and have one pharmacist;
5) submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
7) provide DNA sample;
8) pay court costs;
9) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.
